post_text: Our hearts go out to the families and our community affected by today's storms. If you need assistance, the city will open a temporary shelter at Joe W. Brown Recreation Center (5601 Read Blvd, New Orleans, LA 70127) at 3 p.m. for impacted residents. The New Orleans Health Department, with support from the Red Cross, Catholic Charities, and NOFD, will assist affected individuals. The Regional Transit Authority (RTA) will provide bus transportation to the shelter for affected individuals at the intersections of Dwyer Road and Wilson Avenue; Dwyer Road and Crowder Boulevard; and Dwyer Road and Wright Road.

The special event will take place on Wednesday, February 1, 2017, from 12 p.m. - 1 p.m. at 2045 Lakeshore Drive, CERM Building Suite 438 in New Orleans. RSVP today by emailing tinabouzon@thebrownfoundation.org or barbaragasdaglis@thebrownfoundation.org. For more info, call (504) 834-3433.

post_text: We are so pleased to announce that our very own Mrs. Linda A. Howard-Curtis, school social worker at Pierre A. Capdau Charter School, has been selected by the Louisiana Chapter of the National Association of Social Workers (NASW) to receive the 2016 Louisiana Social Worker of the Year award. She has also earned the distinction of NASW's 2016 School Social Worker of the Year for the Houma/Thibodeaux region. Way to go Mrs. Linda! #capdaupride #NBSF2016

post_text:
***MEDIA ALERT***

ALL NEW BEGINNINGS SCHOOLS FOUNDATION NETWORK OF SCHOOLS WILL BE CLOSED ON FRIDAY MARCH 11

NEW ORLEANS (March 10, 2016) – All New Beginnings Schools Foundation (NBSF) network of schools will be closed on Friday, March 11, 2016 because of projected heavy rainfall. NBSF schools include: Lake Area New Tech Early College High School, Pierre A. Capdau Charter School, Gentilly Terrace Charter School, and Medard H. Nelson Charter School. Classes will resume on Monday, March 14, 2016.
text:
***MEDIA ALERT***

ALL NEW BEGINNINGS SCHOOLS FOUNDATION NETWORK OF SCHOOLS WILL BE CLOSED ON FRIDAY MARCH 11

NEW ORLEANS (March 10, 2016) – All New Beginnings Schools Foundation (NBSF) network of schools will be closed on Friday, March 11, 2016 because of projected heavy rainfall. NBSF schools include: Lake Area New Tech Early College High School, Pierre A. Capdau Charter School, Gentilly Terrace Charter School, and Medard H. Nelson Charter School. Classes will resume on Monday, March 14, 2016.

post_text: Hot off the New Beginnings Press! NBSF was the only charter organization in New Orleans selected to participate in the 2015 Louisiana Principal Fellowship. Pierre A. Capdau Charter School principal Rulonda Green, Medard H. Nelson Charter School principal Chauncey Nash, Gentilly Terrace Charter School principal Edward Brown, and Lake Area New Tech Early College High School principal Darren Lewis were selected to participate in the fellowship. Our Chief Academic Officer Juaquana Stewart was also selected to participate. CONGRATS EVERYONE! #NBSF2015

post_text:
Medard Nelson Band places first in Class Got Brass competition
For the second consecutive year, the Medard Nelson Charter School Band placed first in the Beginners category at the fourth annual Class Got Brass competition, which took place on March 22, 2015, at Louis Armstrong Park in New Orleans.
The Roadrunner band won $4,000 in band instruments. Class Got Brass is sponsored by the New Orleans Jazz & Heritage Foundation and coincided with the foundation’s Congo Square New World Rhythms Festival.

It's the final week of voting!
Vote for Lake Area's Milton Taylor - Finalist in Drew Brees' Trust Your Crazy Ideas Challenge

Vote online: http://trustyourcrazyideaschallenge.org/?contestants=team-7 via any electronic device.

Milton Taylor, a 9th grade student at Lake Area High School, is a finalist in Drew Brees' Trust Your Crazy Ideas Challenge. The judges have cast their votes and deemed Miltons "Crazy Idea" as good enough to be a winner, it's up to the voting public now to decide.
Milton has done his part, now lets do ours as leaders.

The winner from the select group of finalist will be determined a s a result of publicized virtual voting! Votes will be accepted from February 9-27, 2015 (midnight on both days).

This is the only time teachers, parents and friends will have to vote for their favorite idea! Each person can vote once a day.

Vote for Lake Area's Milton Taylor - Finalist in Drew Brees' Trust Your Crazy Ideas Challenge

Milton Taylor, a 9th grade student at Lake Area High School, is a finalist in Drew Brees' Trust Your Crazy Ideas Challenge. The judges have cast their votes and deemed Miltons "Crazy Idea" as good enough to be a winner, it's up to the voting public now to decide.
Milton has done his part, now lets do ours as leaders.

The winner from the select group of finalist will be determined a s a result of publicized virtual voting! Votes will be accepted from February 9-27, 2015 (midnight on both days).

This is the only time teachers, parents and friends will have to vote for their favorite idea! Each person can vote once a day.

Vote online: http://trustyourcrazyideaschallenge.org/?contestants=team-7 via any electronic device.
